  "name": "Case A — Good Fit Fresh CV",
  "summary": "Power Platform and M365 automation practitioner who turns HR, legal, and operational workflows into governed low-code solutions, adoption dashboards, and supportable handoffs. Grounded experience spans Power Apps, Power Automate, SharePoint-backed routing, Power BI visibility, documentation, and production troubleshooting for business users.",
  "content": "# Li Ting Kao / Christine Kao\n\nLi Ting Kao / Christine Kao\nTarget: Power Platform Developer\nTaipei\n\n## Summary\n\nPower Platform and M365 automation practitioner who turns HR, legal, and operational workflows into governed low-code solutions, adoption dashboards, and supportable handoffs. Grounded experience spans Power Apps, Power Automate, SharePoint-backed routing, Power BI visibility, documentation, and production troubleshooting for business users.\n\n## Skills\n\nPower Platform / M365: Power Apps, Power Automate, SharePoint Lists, Power BI, Microsoft 365 Copilot, Workflow automation, Governance documentation, Production troubleshooting, Stakeholder handoff\n\n## Work Experience\n\nBusiness Process Engineer / IS BA | Trend Micro | 2021 - 2026\nSection: Power Platform Workflow Delivery\n- Built a Power Apps and SharePoint-backed DPIA / AI impact assessment workflow with automated routing, reviewer controls, and governance-ready process visibility.\n- Created a self-service mentor booking workflow using form intake and SharePoint lists so HR program users could manage requests without manual spreadsheet tracking.\n- Supported production HR automation flows after handover, connecting Power Automate, Workday RaaS API, Dataverse, SharePoint, Jenkins, and Power BI operating signals.\nSection: Support, Documentation, and Adoption Analytics\n- Authored low-code automation and API engagement documentation covering roles, connection ownership, environment handoff, and maintainability expectations.\n- Stabilized recruiting sync flows by resolving data and flow defects across Power Automate, Workday RaaS API, and SharePoint handoff paths.\n- Built M365 Copilot usage and adoption dashboard views from audit, license, and distribution-list data to give stakeholders clearer adoption visibility.\n- Managed M365 Copilot trial conversion operations using usage reporting, vendor coordination, and license follow-up.\n\nData Engineer & Tableau Dashboard Development Sales Specialist | Advanced Communication Technology & Solutions Corporation | 2016 - 2020\nSection: Data and Dashboard Foundation\n- Delivered dashboard and data-support work that built the analytics foundation later reused in HR and workflow visibility projects.\n- Coordinated technical solution support and project documentation for client delivery teams, strengthening business-to-technology handoff habits.\n\n## Education\n\nAI/Big Data Analysis | TibaMe | 2020/02 - 2020/08\n\nMaster of Biomedical Sciences | Chang Gung University | 2009/07 - 2011/08\n\n## Languages\n\nChinese | Native\nEnglish | Professional",
